        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-04-10 09:24:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > cool. Do not understand even what those testinfra tricks does\n > \n > Well, you just directly connect to another host and issue stuff on\n > it by using testinfra.get_host(\"hostname\").\n\nThe reasoning is that you cannot get facts from testinfra so you cannot get computed cluster_ip value in any possible way. nor you can gather them. so I tried to get ip directly using testinfra itself, by connecting using docker container name, the same way molecule itself and the ansible_runner thing arranges this.",
